Description: Problem~~~~ The tone knob has been pulled out of the electronics, please see pictures (It will need to be repaired) The tone knob and post are included The Volume Knob and selector switch still work fine The original owner switched the bridge plate from the Fender Bridge to a Wilkinson Bridge The original Fender bridge is included,, please see pictures ~~~~ Serial Number N 3 59770 Made in USA After researching the serial number on the internet,,,, I believe this guitar is from 1993 or 1994 If anyone knows the exact model or year of this telecaster, could you please e-mail me ~~~~~ The guitar displays fine as shown in the pictures If you look closely you'll notice some light or small nicks, scuffs and scratches here and there,, please see pictures,,, There is a bigger nick on the back of the body at the top of the horn,,, please see pictures Overall it was well taken care of and is in very nice condition,, aside from the broken Tone Knob,, ~~~ My friend who plays guitar tested it out and this is what he told me: The guitar is pretty much ready to go out of the case aside from the broken tone knob The string action seems high for a Telecaster, but he likes his strings right on the neck All functions work Properly The new owner may want to give it a general maintenance set up to their playing specifications and clean the electronics from dust He played some Rolling Stones songs Brown Sugar and Monkey Man,, to me they sounded really good Comes with a fender hardshell coffin case,, they case key is missing The case shows a good amount of age and storage wear My pictures represent how this guitar looks on display from 3' feet away in a well lit room Shipping weight is between 14 and 15 pounds
Title: Made in USA FENDER TELECASTER Electric Guitar Really Nice Cool Finish
